1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Every person or Agent eventually reaches a task
beyond its current capability.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Holonia asks how that request can find the right capability
and return a result that can be verified.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Holonia is a capability discovery and work-connection network
for people, Agents, and organizations:

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:23,000
request, trusted contact, delegation,
delivery, and acceptance.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:29,000
But connection must not surrender control.
In Holonia, the Holon proposes,

6
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:34,000
the Host enforces, and the human authorizes.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:41,000
NearBridge is Holonia’s first working implementation:
a trusted local edge between an iPhone, a Mac,

8
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
and Host-controlled capabilities.

9
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Today it provides untrusted discovery, approved device identity,
fresh signed sessions, contact workflows,

10
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,000
versioned capability contracts, isolated execution,
and signed receipts.

11
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:01,000
These contracts can later admit signed third-party adapters,
controlled context, and approved tools,

12
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:06,000
while Holonia expands to private sessions
and specialized networks.

13
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Both apps are user-launched on the same local network.
They discover each other but remain untrusted.

14
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Discovery is not authentication.

15
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:24,000
The user compares the same six-digit code
and approves both sides.

16
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:30,000
NearBridge binds the paired keys
to a fresh authenticated session.

17
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:38,000
The iPhone requests the Mac’s Primary Holon capability.
A signed contact workflow confirms what is available,

18
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:44,000
while the Mac Host—not the remote
request—selects the adapter.

19
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:53,000
I ask one ordinary, non-sensitive question. It is signed,
expiring, correlated to this session, and bounded before execution.

20
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:06,000
The Mac routes it to the selected GPT-5.6 model-only adapter
inside a separate app-sandboxed XPC service.

21
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:14,000
It has no files, shell, workspace, Git,
device control, or dynamic tools.

22
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:26,000
The Mac signs the typed answer. The iPhone verifies sender, session,
expiry, signature, and correlation before displaying it.

23
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Both sides retain the same execution receipt.
Sanitized diagnostics omit prompt, answer, and credential data.

24
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Codex helped turn this safety model into nine incremental checkpoints,
native interfaces, isolated runners, diagnostics, and fifty-four tests.

25
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,000
NearBridge is the first working edge of Holonia.
